<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="448" pageId="3" pageNumber="446" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1256,2039]" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1364,1390]" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">Description.</emphasis>
Body length without antennae 2.2–2.6 mm. Colour in alcohol bluish-grey, ocular plate bluishblack. Tegumental granulation strong. Antennae as long as head. Ant. I with 7 chaetae, Ant. II with 11 chaetae and Ant. III with 18 ordinary chaetae. Ant. III and IV fused dorsally, ventral separation well marked. Sensory organ of Ant. III consisting of two small, globular internal sensilla, two subcylindrical guard sensilla (ventral sensillum is 1.3 times as long as dorsal one) and two guard chaetae between them; ventral microsensillum present. Ant. IV with about 40 ordinary chaetae, 7–8 short and truncate chaetae in ventro-apical part and 6 distinct subcylindrical sensilla; dorsoexternal microsensillum and subapical organite present; apical vesicle trilobed (
<figureCitation box="[1105,1235,1580,1606]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–19" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1965,1989]" captionTargetBox="[177,1411,433,1930]" captionTargetId="figure-159@5.[163,1425,417,1942]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 12–19. Pseudachorutes kurdistanicus sp. nov. 12, dorsal chaetotaxy of body; 13, Ant. III and IV dorsally; 14, Ant. III and IV ventrally; 15, labial chaetotaxy; 16, PAO and eyes; 17, distal part of leg III; 18, furca; 19, chaetotaxy of Abds. I–VI." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6623161" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6623161/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">Figs 13, 14</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1256,2039]" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">
PAO round with 11–12 vesicles, ca. as long as ocellus B (
<figureCitation box="[861,946,1616,1643]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–19" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1965,1989]" captionTargetBox="[177,1411,433,1930]" captionTargetId="figure-159@5.[163,1425,417,1942]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 12–19. Pseudachorutes kurdistanicus sp. nov. 12, dorsal chaetotaxy of body; 13, Ant. III and IV dorsally; 14, Ant. III and IV ventrally; 15, labial chaetotaxy; 16, PAO and eyes; 17, distal part of leg III; 18, furca; 19, chaetotaxy of Abds. I–VI." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6623161" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6623161/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
). 8+8 eyes. Buccal cone relatively short as 1.2 Ant. I lengths. Mandibles invisible. Styliform maxilla with two lamellae, one of them with tiny apical hook (as on 
<figureCitation box="[186,254,1688,1714]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–11" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,192,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[152,1436,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–11. Pseudachorutes hyrcanicus sp. nov. 1, dorsal chaetotaxy of body; 2, central area of head between d3 and d5 chaetae; 3, Ant. III and IV ventrally; 4, Ant. III and IV dorsally; 5a, chaetotaxy of labrum; 5b, labial chaetotaxy; 6, PAO and eyes; 7, distal part of leg III; 8, mandible; 9, maxilla; 10, furca; 11, chaetotaxy of Abds. II–VI." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6623159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6623159/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). Labral formula: 4/2,3,4 (as on 
<figureCitation box="[618,699,1688,1715]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–11" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,192,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[152,1436,179,1917]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–11. Pseudachorutes hyrcanicus sp. nov. 1, dorsal chaetotaxy of body; 2, central area of head between d3 and d5 chaetae; 3, Ant. III and IV ventrally; 4, Ant. III and IV dorsally; 5a, chaetotaxy of labrum; 5b, labial chaetotaxy; 6, PAO and eyes; 7, distal part of leg III; 8, mandible; 9, maxilla; 10, furca; 11, chaetotaxy of Abds. II–VI." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6623159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6623159/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">Fig. 5a</figureCitation>
). Labium without organites x and papillate chaetae L, with 11+11 ordinary chaetae (
<figureCitation box="[352,436,1724,1751]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–19" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1965,1989]" captionTargetBox="[177,1411,433,1930]" captionTargetId="figure-159@5.[163,1425,417,1942]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 12–19. Pseudachorutes kurdistanicus sp. nov. 12, dorsal chaetotaxy of body; 13, Ant. III and IV dorsally; 14, Ant. III and IV ventrally; 15, labial chaetotaxy; 16, PAO and eyes; 17, distal part of leg III; 18, furca; 19, chaetotaxy of Abds. I–VI." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6623161" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6623161/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
). Perilabial area with 4+4 subequal chaetae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1256,2039]" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">
Dorsal chaetotaxy as in 
<figureCitation box="[478,560,1760,1786]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–19" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1965,1989]" captionTargetBox="[177,1411,433,1930]" captionTargetId="figure-159@5.[163,1425,417,1942]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 12–19. Pseudachorutes kurdistanicus sp. nov. 12, dorsal chaetotaxy of body; 13, Ant. III and IV dorsally; 14, Ant. III and IV ventrally; 15, labial chaetotaxy; 16, PAO and eyes; 17, distal part of leg III; 18, furca; 19, chaetotaxy of Abds. I–VI." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6623161" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6623161/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
with very short chaetae and with short sensory S-chaetae. Formula per half tergum as: 022/11111. Microsensilla 
<emphasis box="[562,593,1797,1822]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">ms</emphasis>
on Tht. II and III present. Head with unpaired chaeta 
