<figureCitation box="[642,724,1976,2002]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–19" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1965,1989]" captionTargetBox="[177,1411,433,1930]" captionTargetId="figure-159@5.[163,1425,417,1942]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 12–19. Pseudachorutes kurdistanicus sp. nov. 12, dorsal chaetotaxy of body; 13, Ant. III and IV dorsally; 14, Ant. III and IV ventrally; 15, labial chaetotaxy; 16, PAO and eyes; 17, distal part of leg III; 18, furca; 19, chaetotaxy of Abds. I–VI." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6623161" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6623161/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="446">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
