12, dorsal chaetotaxy of body; 13, Ant. III and IV dorsally; 14, Ant. III and IV ventrally; 15, labial chaetotaxy; 16, PAO and eyes; 17, distal part of leg III; 18, furca; 19, chaetotaxy of Abds. I–VI.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="449" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,151,465]" pageId="6" pageNumber="449">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,151,177]" pageId="6" pageNumber="449">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name of the new species refers to the 
<collectingRegion box="[842,1062,151,177]" country="Iran" name="Kordestan" pageId="6" pageNumber="449">Kurdistan Province</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry box="[1080,1130,151,177]" name="Iran" pageId="6" pageNumber="449">Iran</collectingCountry>
), the place where the 
<typeStatus box="[1388,1436,151,177]" pageId="6" pageNumber="449">type</typeStatus>
specimens were collected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="449" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,151,465]" pageId="6" pageNumber="449">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,222,248]" pageId="6" pageNumber="449">Discussion.</emphasis>
The same 
<typeStatus box="[452,500,223,249]" pageId="6" pageNumber="449">type</typeStatus>
of chaetotaxy of head (present unpaired chaeta 
<emphasis box="[1030,1044,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="449">d</emphasis>
1 and absent 
<emphasis box="[1188,1202,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="449">a</emphasis>
0 chaeta), Tht. I (3+3 chaetae), Tht. II-III (10+10 chaetae each, 
<emphasis box="[623,637,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="449">a</emphasis>
2 chaeta absent), Abdt. I-III (8+8 chaetae each, 
<emphasis box="[1177,1197,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="449">m</emphasis>
row chaetae absent), Abdt. IV (9+9(10) chaetae, [
<emphasis box="[478,498,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="449">m</emphasis>
6±]), Abdt. V (5+5 chaetae, 
<emphasis box="[822,836,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="449">a</emphasis>
2 and 
<emphasis box="[908,922,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="449">p</emphasis>
2 chaetae absent) and furca (six chaetae), the absence of lateral teeth on claws indicate a close relationship between 
<taxonomicName authority="Shayanmehr &amp; Kaprus’ &amp; Ghobari &amp; Yahyapour &amp; Samani &amp; Lafooraki &amp; Sepanlou, 2022" authorityName="Shayanmehr &amp; Kaprus’ &amp; Ghobari &amp; Yahyapour &amp; Samani &amp; Lafooraki &amp; Sepanlou" authorityYear="2022" box="[947,1125,331,357]" class="Collembola" family="Neanuridae" genus="Pseudachorutes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="6" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kurdistanicus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[947,1125,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="449">P. kurdistanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1133,1224,331,357]" pageId="6" pageNumber="449" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1133,1218,331,357]" pageId="6" pageNumber="449">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kaprus, IJ &amp; Weiner, WM" authorityYear="2009" box="[1239,1340,331,357]" class="Collembola" family="Neanuridae" genus="Pseudachorutes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="6" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vasylii">
<emphasis box="[1239,1340,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="449">P. vasylii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kaprus’ &amp; 
<bibRefCitation author="Weiner, W." box="[179,328,367,393]" pageId="6" pageNumber="449" pagination="1 - 23" refId="ref5423" refString="Kaprus', I. J. &amp; Weiner, W. (2009) The genus Pseudachorutes Tullberg, 1871 (Collembola, Neanuridae) in the Ukraine with descriptions of new species. Zootaxa, 2166 (1), 1 - 23. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2166.1.1" type="journal article" year="2009">Weiner, 2009</bibRefCitation>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Arbea &amp; Jordana, 1989" authorityName="Arbea &amp; Jordana" authorityYear="1989" box="[382,750,367,393]" class="Collembola" family="Neanuridae" genus="Pseudachorutes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="6" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laricis">
<emphasis box="[382,481,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="449">P. laricis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Arbea, J. I. &amp; Jordana, R." box="[486,750,367,393]" pageId="6" pageNumber="449" pagination="157 - 166" refId="ref5150" refString="Arbea, J. I. &amp; Jordana, R. (1989) The Genus Pseudachorutes (Collembola, Neanuridae) from Navarra (Northern Iberian Peninsula), with description of a new species and a new subspecies. Mitteilungen der Schweitzerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 62, 157 - 166." type="journal article" year="1989">Arbea &amp; Jordana, 1989</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. These species differ distinctly in number of vesicles in PAO, shape of apical vesicle on Ant. IV, details of labium chaetotaxy, labral formula of chaetae, number of chaetae on VT and tibiotarsi of legs I-III (Table 1).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
